      </svg></div>
      <div class="stack-lg">
        <p class="t-lead t-pretty">Fragmentation is not a failure. It is what living systems do when more is asked of them than they can metabolise — the parts go quiet, go underground, split off, keep working alone. They are still loyal; they just stopped trusting the room.</p>
        <p class="t-body t-pretty">Wholeness is not the absence of those parts. It is their return. One by one, gently, in their own time, they come back into the room. They do not need to be fixed. They need to be welcomed.</p>
        <p class="t-body t-pretty">There is no point on the arc where the work is finished. There are only longer and longer stretches where everything in you is invited to belong.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
